    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Barrow-Sentinels are the most ancient of the barrow-dead Ã¢â‚¬â€ warriors interred at the foundations of Svellheim's oldest grave-complexes, their bodies half-fused with stone and ancient rune-iron over centuries of cold slumber. They do not stalk or pursue Ã¢â‚¬â€ they <em>wait</em>, entombed upright in crypt alcoves until the living intrude. When awakened, they rise with a grinding sound like glaciers calving, wielding stone-encased mauls that shatter bone and drive foes into the ice. The runes carved into their skulls at burial blind them to fear and deaden them to cold Ã¢â‚¬â€ they are simply obstacles, patient and immovable as the barrows themselves.</p>",
